        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>School Social Workers Improving Student Success Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965 to authorize the Department of Education to award renewable grants to high-need local educational agencies to retain or hire additional school social workers.</p> <p>Grantees may use the funds to reimburse school social workers for expenses they incur in rendering services.</p> <p>Grant-funded social workers must target their services to the highest-need students.</p> <p>Grant funds may not be used to supplant other funds used for hiring and retaining school social workers.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
